China on Monday called on South Korea to work with it to fend off the risk of a new Cold War. Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi made the appeal during talks with Park Jin, South Korea's new foreign minister under the newly- inaugurated President Yoon Suk-yeol, via video link. It serves the fundamental interests of China and South Korea to continue to keep the region open and inclusive, prevent the risk of a new Cold War and oppose bloc confrontation, said Wang. He said China is pleased to see South Korea play a a more constructive role in promoting world peace and prosperity. China stands ready to work with it to safeguard the common interests of the two countries, of Asia at large and of emerging markets so as to inject stability and certainty into a turbulent time, said Wang. (Cover: Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi (L) hold talks with South Korean Foreign Minister Park Jin via video link, May 16, 2022. /Chinese Foreign Ministry)